data.event: Today Aberdeen retains many historic structures from this period, with over 200 buildings on the National Register of Historic Places.
The most prominent of these antebellum homes is The Magnolias, which was built in 1850.
Aberdeen was first settled in 1834 and chartered as a town in 1837.
